1
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:34,202
ARO: Ah!

2
00:00:34,235 --> 00:00:36,770
Valentina has
brought us something.

3
00:00:36,804 --> 00:00:38,339
She should not have interrupted.

4
00:00:39,207 --> 00:00:40,741
She's new.

5
00:00:40,774 --> 00:00:42,410
Aren't they all?

6
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:10,238
Ah!

7
00:01:10,271 --> 00:01:13,741
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

8
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:17,478
Edward and Bella
are to be married.

9
00:01:17,845 --> 00:01:21,115
What joy!

10
00:01:21,149 --> 00:01:23,551
This is the Cullens' way of
announcing her transformation.

11
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:27,355
They mock us with their delays.

12
00:01:27,388 --> 00:01:29,223
Patience, brother.

13
00:01:34,628 --> 00:01:36,197
Though you do have a point.

14
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:40,434
The human did interrupt.

15
00:01:43,271 --> 00:01:45,739
Oh, I do love weddings.

16
00:01:48,176 --> 00:01:49,677
No!

17
00:02:09,763 --> 00:02:12,566
BELLA: "Childhood is not
from birth to a certain age.

18
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:18,539
"And at a certain age, the child is
grown and puts away childish things.

19
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:29,450
"Childhood is the kingdom
where nobody dies."

20
00:02:37,691 --> 00:02:39,360
Jake! Jacob!

21
00:02:41,929 --> 00:02:43,764
(ROARING)

22
00:03:09,957 --> 00:03:10,824
Phil!

23
00:03:16,264 --> 00:03:17,565
It's happening.

24
00:03:21,469 --> 00:03:22,836
(SCRAPING)

25
00:03:30,844 --> 00:03:32,746
You just have to break them in.

26
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:35,983
I've been breaking them in.
For three days.

27
00:03:36,016 --> 00:03:37,351
Can I just go barefoot?

28
00:03:37,385 --> 00:03:39,720
No, absolutely not.

29
00:03:39,753 --> 00:03:41,789
Just thinking it's
a little much, you know?

30
00:03:41,822 --> 00:03:44,292
The dress and the shoes,

31
00:03:44,325 --> 00:03:45,326
and all of this.

32
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,763
ALICE:
No, it's exactly enough.

33
00:03:49,797 --> 00:03:52,500
Tomorrow will be perfect.

34
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:53,901
Where do you want them, boss?

35
00:03:53,934 --> 00:03:54,735
On either side of the aisle.

36
00:03:56,504 --> 00:03:58,706
What aisle?
Does no one have vision?

37
00:04:17,024 --> 00:04:19,627
You, go home and get
lots of beauty sleep.

38
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,694
That's an order.

39
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:22,996
Okay.

40
00:05:10,678 --> 00:05:12,746
I was just checking
for cold feet.

41
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:18,552
Well, mine are toasty warm.

42
00:05:18,586 --> 00:05:20,120
It's not too late
to change your mind.

43
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:21,755
What? Now you're
having second thoughts?

44
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:25,759
You are.

45
00:05:28,862 --> 00:05:30,731
No, I've been waiting a
century to marry you, Miss Swan.

46
00:05:32,132 --> 00:05:33,066
But?

47
00:05:34,902 --> 00:05:35,703
But?

48
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:40,140
I haven't told you
everything about myself.

49
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:41,442
What? You're not a virgin?

50
00:05:41,475 --> 00:05:42,710
(LAUGHS)

51
00:05:49,717 --> 00:05:51,118
(EXHALING)

52
00:05:51,151 --> 00:05:53,621
Look, you can't
scare me away now.

53
00:05:56,624 --> 00:05:59,359
Look, a few years
after Carlisle created me,

54
00:06:00,761 --> 00:06:02,463
I rebelled against him.

55
00:06:03,831 --> 00:06:06,166
I resented him for
curbing my appetite.

56
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:09,069
And so for a while,
I went off on my own.

57
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:11,138
I wanted to know
how it felt to hunt.

58
00:06:11,171 --> 00:06:12,673
(SCREAMING)

59
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:13,707
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMS)

60
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:19,046
EDWARD: To taste human blood.

61
00:07:09,497 --> 00:07:10,531
(HEART BEATING RAPIDLY)

62
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:11,499
(CHOKING)

63
00:07:14,902 --> 00:07:16,103
All the men I killed

64
00:07:18,572 --> 00:07:19,907
were monsters.

65
00:07:24,612 --> 00:07:25,879
And so was I.

66
00:07:31,218 --> 00:07:32,653
Edward, they were all murderers.

67
00:07:34,555 --> 00:07:37,991
You probably saved
more lives than you took.

68
00:07:38,025 --> 00:07:40,894
Bella, that's what
I told myself.

69
00:07:40,928 --> 00:07:44,164
But they were all human beings.

70
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:48,101
I looked into their eyes as
they died and I saw who I was,

71
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:49,903
and what I was capable of.

72
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:56,143
And what I'll be capable of.

73
00:07:56,176 --> 00:07:58,078
Why are you
telling me this tonight?

74
00:07:58,111 --> 00:08:00,781
Did you really think this was
gonna change my mind about you?

75
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:04,552
I just wondered if it would
change your mind about yourself,

76
00:08:04,585 --> 00:08:06,720
and who you wanna see when you
look in the mirror a year from now.

77
00:08:10,891 --> 00:08:13,060
I know I can do this.

78
00:08:13,093 --> 00:08:14,895
Let me tell you why.

79
00:08:14,928 --> 00:08:16,664
Because you did.

80
00:08:16,697 --> 00:08:18,566
(SCOFFS)

81
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:19,833
You should give yourself
some credit for that.

82
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:23,236
Now, hopefully, a year from now,

83
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:27,708
I'm gonna look in the mirror
and see someone like you.

84
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:33,013
I mean, someone capable of
courage and sacrifice and love.

85
00:08:38,952 --> 00:08:40,954
(EMMETT WHISTLES)
What is that?

86
00:08:40,988 --> 00:08:41,989
EMMETT: Come on! Let's go!
I'm late for my bachelor party.

87
00:08:44,592 --> 00:08:46,026
Send him out, Bella,
or we're coming in after him.

88
00:08:47,995 --> 00:08:49,296
So, this party.

89
00:08:50,664 --> 00:08:52,700
Will there be strippers?

90
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:54,802
(LAUGHS)

91
00:08:54,835 --> 00:08:59,673
No, just a couple of mountain
lions. Maybe a few bears.

92
00:08:59,707 --> 00:09:01,675
Don't worry, Bella, we'll give
him back in plenty of time.

93
00:09:03,143 --> 00:09:05,245
Okay, go, before
they break my house.

94
00:09:05,278 --> 00:09:07,014
EMMETT: Let's go! Let's go!

95
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:16,924
I'll meet you at the altar.

96
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:20,728
I'll be the one in white.

97
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,130
That was very convincing.

98
00:09:25,165 --> 00:09:26,566
(ALL LAUGHING)

99
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:15,308
What did I say
about beauty sleep?

100
00:11:15,342 --> 00:11:17,210
Sorry, bad dream.

101
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:21,148
It was wedding jitters.

102
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:25,318
Do you need some help?

103
00:11:25,352 --> 00:11:27,120
I could do her hair.

104
00:11:28,055 --> 00:11:29,089
Really?

105
00:11:33,326 --> 00:11:37,130
Please. I'm not offended
by your choice of groom.

106
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:40,033
Just my blatant lack of
respect for mortality.

107
00:11:41,268 --> 00:11:42,469
Essentially.

108
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:46,774
Weddings. They bring
everyone together.

109
00:11:48,809 --> 00:11:50,911
Hey, so, did you find
our daughter?

110
00:11:50,944 --> 00:11:52,813
Are those graduation caps?

111
00:11:53,847 --> 00:11:56,049
(LAUGHS) How creative!

112
00:11:57,785 --> 00:11:58,986
Or weird.

113
00:11:59,019 --> 00:12:00,120
Alice? Bella?

114
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:01,421
BELLA: In here, Mom.

115
00:12:06,026 --> 00:12:07,995
(GASPS) Oh, my gosh!

116
00:12:08,028 --> 00:12:10,230
You're so beautiful.

117
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:12,032
Oh, honey.

118
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:13,100
Crap! My mascara.

119
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:14,201
Mom!

120
00:12:14,835 --> 00:12:16,069
Thanks.

121
00:12:17,437 --> 00:12:18,271
Charlie, get in here.

122
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:22,242
You sure? I don't wanna...

123
00:12:28,315 --> 00:12:30,083
I know. I look hot.

124
00:12:30,117 --> 00:12:32,319
(LAUGHING)

125
00:12:32,352 --> 00:12:33,486
We thought you
needed something blue.

126
00:12:34,922 --> 00:12:36,189
And something old.

127
00:12:36,223 --> 00:12:38,225
Besides your mother.
(SCOFFS) Nice.

128
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:42,129
It was Grandma Swan's.

129
00:12:42,162 --> 00:12:43,964
But we added the sapphires.

130
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:45,933
It's beautiful, you guys.

131
00:12:45,966 --> 00:12:48,335
Wow. Thank you so much.

132
00:12:48,368 --> 00:12:50,270
It's your first family heirloom.

133
00:12:52,072 --> 00:12:56,043
Pass on to your daughter,
and her daughter.

134
00:13:02,182 --> 00:13:03,851
Mom, I love it.

135
00:13:03,884 --> 00:13:06,219
Nope. No smudging
my masterpiece.

136
00:13:06,253 --> 00:13:07,254
She's right.

137
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:11,558
Thank you.

138
00:13:15,028 --> 00:13:16,830
ALICE: Okay.

139
00:13:16,864 --> 00:13:19,166
Time for the dress!

140
00:13:19,199 --> 00:13:21,001
(GASPS)

141
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:23,937
ALICE: Do you wanna see it?
RENEE: I want to see it!

142
00:13:23,971 --> 00:13:25,472
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

143
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:38,818
ERIC: They have
got to be related.

144
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,454
What a gene pool.

145
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:42,990
ERIC: Seriously.

146
00:13:43,023 --> 00:13:45,225
You've got some...
The drool.

147
00:13:48,295 --> 00:13:51,865
So, you think
Bella's gonna be showing?

148
00:13:51,899 --> 00:13:53,533
Jess, she is not pregnant.

149
00:13:53,566 --> 00:13:56,236
Okay. Who else
gets married at 18?

150
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,075
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

151
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,893
(SIGHING)

152
00:14:19,927 --> 00:14:21,061
You ready?

153
00:14:22,495 --> 00:14:23,296
(SOFTLY) Yeah.

154
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,303
Just don't let me fall, Dad.

155
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:32,372
Never.

156
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:41,668
MINISTER: Ladies and gentlemen,
we are gathered here on this glorious day

157
00:16:41,701 --> 00:16:45,372
to witness the union of
Edward Cullen and Bella Swan.

158
00:16:46,539 --> 00:16:49,076
Please repeat after me.

159
00:16:49,109 --> 00:16:50,743
I, Edward Cullen.

160
00:16:50,777 --> 00:16:53,246
I, Edward Cullen.

161
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,715
- MINISTER: Take you, Bella Swan.
- EDWARD: Take you, Bella Swan.

162
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:57,184
MINISTER: To have and to hold.

163
00:16:57,217 --> 00:16:59,119
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

164
00:17:00,787 --> 00:17:02,522
To have and to hold.

165
00:17:04,191 --> 00:17:05,725
For better or for worse.

166
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:07,494
For richer, for poorer.

167
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:11,464
In sickness and in health.

168
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,734
To love.

169
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:17,137
To cherish.

170
00:17:18,538 --> 00:17:20,307
As long as we both shall live.

171
00:17:22,809 --> 00:17:23,810
I do.

172
00:17:24,744 --> 00:17:25,545
I do.

173
00:17:28,281 --> 00:17:29,282
I love you.

174
00:17:29,816 --> 00:17:31,184
I love you.

175
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:34,821
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

176
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:32,879
(PLAYING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

177
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:38,151
Just thought it'd be bigger.

178
00:18:38,185 --> 00:18:39,419
Yeah.

179
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:41,554
Hi!
Hi, guys.

180
00:18:41,588 --> 00:18:43,656
We were just saying how pretty
everything is, you know, just saying.

181
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:45,725
Well, thanks so much.
You don't think it's too much?

182
00:18:45,758 --> 00:18:47,427
No.
Not at all.

183
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:49,229
No.
No.

184
00:18:49,262 --> 00:18:51,764
Hey, man. Nice to see you.

185
00:18:51,798 --> 00:18:53,900
I'm happy for you.
Thank you.

186
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,868
I hope you'll be happy, Bella.

187
00:18:55,902 --> 00:18:58,305
Thank you, Billy.

188
00:18:58,338 --> 00:18:59,606
Have you heard from him?

189
00:18:59,639 --> 00:19:01,274
I'm sure Jake
wishes you the best.

190
00:19:03,576 --> 00:19:06,946
Well, I plan on getting drunk.

191
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,748
They're serving up
some pretty fancy champagne.

192
00:19:08,781 --> 00:19:11,318
Sue, can I get you a glass?

193
00:19:11,351 --> 00:19:12,685
Sparkling fire water.

194
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:14,521
Sounds great.

195
00:19:17,590 --> 00:19:18,391
CARMEN: Bella.

196
00:19:20,527 --> 00:19:21,861
Congratulations, Edward.
Thank you.

197
00:19:21,894 --> 00:19:23,330
Bella.

198
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:24,531
Eleazar and Carmen, right?

199
00:19:24,564 --> 00:19:25,832
Mmm-hmm.
Hola.

200
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:27,534
Yes, and these are
our cousins from Alaska.

201
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,769
Tanya, Kate. We've
heard so much about you.

202
00:19:29,802 --> 00:19:30,703
Welcome to the family.
Bienvenida.

203
00:19:31,638 --> 00:19:32,639
BELLA: Thank you.

204
00:19:37,477 --> 00:19:38,545
Irina.

205
00:19:39,779 --> 00:19:40,580
Come meet Bella.

206
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:47,754
I can't do this.
You promised.

207
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:51,624
They invited one.

208
00:19:58,365 --> 00:19:59,832
Irina, he's our friend.

209
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:01,634
They killed Laurent.

210
00:20:01,668 --> 00:20:02,569
He tried to kill Bella.

211
00:20:03,703 --> 00:20:05,572
I don't believe that.

212
00:20:05,605 --> 00:20:07,674
He wanted to be like us.

213
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:09,842
To live in peace with humans.

214
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:10,910
With me.

215
00:20:11,844 --> 00:20:13,212
I'm sorry.

216
00:20:15,382 --> 00:20:16,449
CARMEN: Irina!
ELEAZAR: Well.

217
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:21,321
Let's not monopolize
the bride. Congratulations.

218
00:20:21,354 --> 00:20:22,489
BELLA: Thank you.

219
00:20:22,522 --> 00:20:23,656
Sorry.

220
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:28,495
Well, what's a wedding
without some family drama?

221
00:20:28,528 --> 00:20:29,896
Yeah.
EMMETT: Excuse me.

222
00:20:29,929 --> 00:20:31,398
Is this on?

223
00:20:32,432 --> 00:20:33,666
Hello?

224
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:34,767
(MAN WOLF-WHISTLES)

225
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:36,703
Umm...

226
00:20:37,704 --> 00:20:40,039
I'd like to propose a toast.

227
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:42,942
To my new sister.

228
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:46,779
Bella, I hope you've gotten
enough sleep these last 18 years.

229
00:20:46,813 --> 00:20:49,649
'Cause you won't be getting
any more for a while (CHUCKLES)

230
00:20:49,682 --> 00:20:50,917
(SILENCE)

231
00:20:54,821 --> 00:20:59,959
Well, Bella was just like everybody
else, totally mesmerized by Edward.

232
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:02,829
Or "The Hair," as I call him.

233
00:21:05,332 --> 00:21:07,334
And then, suddenly,

234
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:10,903
Edward is all about Bella.

235
00:21:10,937 --> 00:21:14,941
Even though she's not the
captain of the volleyball team.

236
00:21:14,974 --> 00:21:17,410
I'm just kidding.
I'm just kidding.

237
00:21:17,444 --> 00:21:18,845
Or the president of
the student council.

238
00:21:18,878 --> 00:21:20,913
Edward will be a good husband.

239
00:21:22,649 --> 00:21:25,685
I know this because I'm a cop.

240
00:21:26,986 --> 00:21:29,622
I know things.

241
00:21:29,656 --> 00:21:33,526
Like how to hunt somebody
to the ends of the Earth.

242
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,827
(GUESTS LAUGHING)

243
00:21:34,861 --> 00:21:37,530
Now that you're my sister,

244
00:21:37,564 --> 00:21:39,298
you'll have to get over
your aversion to fashion.

245
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,435
And I know how to use a gun.

246
00:21:43,436 --> 00:21:45,738
Skirts, heels, handbags.

247
00:21:45,772 --> 00:21:47,574
(SINGING LULLABY)

248
00:21:59,586 --> 00:22:01,988
I'd like to thank
Renee and Charlie

249
00:22:02,021 --> 00:22:06,959
for bringing such a wonderful
person into the world and into our lives.

250
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:09,862
We will cherish and
protect her forever.

251
00:22:09,896 --> 00:22:12,632
It's an extraordinary thing

252
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:17,036
to meet someone
who you can bare your soul to.

253
00:22:17,069 --> 00:22:19,472
And who will accept
you for what you are.

254
00:22:19,506 --> 00:22:22,675
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

255
00:22:22,709 --> 00:22:25,812
I've been waiting, what
seems like a very long time,

256
00:22:27,747 --> 00:22:29,716
to get beyond what I am.

257
00:22:31,784 --> 00:22:33,119
And with Bella,

258
00:22:35,855 --> 00:22:37,056
I feel like I can finally begin.

259
00:22:42,462 --> 00:22:45,765
So I'd like to propose a toast
to my beautiful bride.

260
00:22:49,536 --> 00:22:53,039
No measure of time with you
will be long enough.

261
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:56,843
But let's start with forever.

262
00:23:03,783 --> 00:23:06,853
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

263
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:11,891
Whoa!

264
00:23:15,462 --> 00:23:16,763
Whoa!

265
00:23:25,938 --> 00:23:28,140
Another one of your
gifts just arrived.

266
00:23:28,174 --> 00:23:28,975
What?

267
00:23:30,810 --> 00:23:31,944
Yeah, come on.

268
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:36,483
What's a wedding
present doing out here?

269
00:23:36,516 --> 00:23:39,085
Just a little more private.

270
00:23:39,118 --> 00:23:41,788
The best man didn't
have time to get a tux.

271
00:23:42,655 --> 00:23:43,656
Jacob!

272
00:23:45,892 --> 00:23:46,859
Jacob.

273
00:23:49,696 --> 00:23:50,663
(BOTH LAUGHING)
Hey.

274
00:23:52,732 --> 00:23:54,934
Hey, Bella.
Hey.

275
00:23:54,967 --> 00:23:56,536
This is kind of you.

276
00:23:56,569 --> 00:23:58,104
Kind is my middle name.

277
00:24:03,042 --> 00:24:05,077
I'll see if
Rosalie wants to dance.

278
00:24:06,746 --> 00:24:08,581
I'm sorry I'm late.

279
00:24:08,615 --> 00:24:09,949
Doesn't matter.

280
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:12,852
Everything's perfect now.

281
00:24:15,522 --> 00:24:16,623
Will you dance with me?

282
00:24:24,931 --> 00:24:26,499
(BOTH LAUGHING)

283
00:24:29,268 --> 00:24:30,169
Where have you been?

284
00:24:32,238 --> 00:24:34,507
We were gonna put your face
on a milk carton.

285
00:24:35,975 --> 00:24:37,677
Mostly northern Canada.

286
00:24:39,078 --> 00:24:41,781
I think.

287
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:46,185
It's weird to be back on
two legs again, in clothes.

288
00:24:46,218 --> 00:24:49,255
Gotten out of practice
with the whole human thing.

289
00:24:52,258 --> 00:24:53,726
Are you okay?

290
00:24:56,295 --> 00:24:57,664
Being here?

291
00:25:00,066 --> 00:25:02,935
Why? Afraid I'll trash
your party?

292
00:25:07,607 --> 00:25:08,941
(SOFT GROWLING)

293
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:13,913
You're not the only one.

294
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:20,052
You'd think I'd be used to
telling you goodbye by now.

295
00:25:24,757 --> 00:25:27,927
Come on, you're not supposed
to be the one crying, Bella.

296
00:25:31,898 --> 00:25:34,000
Everyone cries at weddings.

297
00:25:36,769 --> 00:25:38,905
This is how I'm
gonna remember you.

298
00:25:39,706 --> 00:25:40,907
Pink cheeks.

299
00:25:42,909 --> 00:25:44,243
Two left feet.

300
00:25:50,683 --> 00:25:52,018
Heartbeat.

301
00:25:55,021 --> 00:25:57,590
'Cause what, soon I'm
gonna be dead to you?

302
00:25:57,624 --> 00:25:58,290
No.

303
00:26:09,168 --> 00:26:11,203
I'm sorry.

304
00:26:11,237 --> 00:26:13,239
I'm just trying to appreciate
your last night as a human.

305
00:26:16,308 --> 00:26:17,243
Well, it's not my last night.

306
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:24,617
I thought you...

307
00:26:24,651 --> 00:26:27,754
I didn't really wanna spend
my honeymoon writhing in pain.

308
00:26:27,787 --> 00:26:29,221
What's the point?

309
00:26:32,358 --> 00:26:35,227
It's not like you're gonna have a
real honeymoon with him, anyway.

310
00:26:35,261 --> 00:26:37,697
It's gonna be as
real as anyone else's.

311
00:26:37,730 --> 00:26:38,698
That's a sick joke.

312
00:26:40,266 --> 00:26:41,367
You are joking?

313
00:26:43,870 --> 00:26:45,772
What? While you're
still human?

314
00:26:45,805 --> 00:26:48,240
You can't be serious, Bella.
Tell me you're not that stupid.

315
00:26:50,242 --> 00:26:52,211
I mean, it's really
none of your business.

316
00:26:52,244 --> 00:26:54,413
No! You can't do this!
Jake.

317
00:26:54,446 --> 00:26:56,816
Listen to me, Bella.
Jake, let me go!

318
00:26:56,849 --> 00:26:58,751
Jacob, calm down, all right?

319
00:26:58,785 --> 00:27:00,687
Are you out of your mind? Huh?
You'll kill her!

320
00:27:01,721 --> 00:27:02,321
Walk away, Jake.

321
00:27:08,027 --> 00:27:09,028
Enough, Jacob!

322
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:12,098
Stay out of this, Sam.

323
00:27:12,131 --> 00:27:14,000
You're not gonna start
something that we'll have to finish.

324
00:27:14,033 --> 00:27:15,101
She'll die.

325
00:27:15,134 --> 00:27:16,669
She's not our concern anymore.

326
00:27:36,122 --> 00:27:37,123
Let's go, Seth!

327
00:27:42,494 --> 00:27:44,230
BELLA: I'm really,
really, really stupid.

328
00:27:44,263 --> 00:27:47,900
No, it's all right.

329
00:27:47,934 --> 00:27:51,003
Come on, people are probably
missing us. Let's go back.

330
00:27:55,507 --> 00:27:57,409
(ALL CHEERING)

331
00:28:11,023 --> 00:28:13,459
So, he really won't tell you
where he's taking you?

332
00:28:13,492 --> 00:28:15,094
No, it's a surprise.

333
00:28:15,127 --> 00:28:16,428
(LAUGHS)

334
00:28:18,831 --> 00:28:21,067
Well, wear a hat.

335
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:22,869
Sunscreen.

336
00:28:22,902 --> 00:28:23,770
Take care of yourself.

337
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:25,337
I will.

338
00:28:26,438 --> 00:28:27,373
Okay.

339
00:28:29,976 --> 00:28:31,911
I love you, Bella.

340
00:28:31,944 --> 00:28:33,112
I love you.

341
00:28:33,846 --> 00:28:35,081
So much.

342
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:44,490
Thank you.

343
00:28:53,866 --> 00:28:55,134
Everything's
packed and ready to go.

344
00:28:56,202 --> 00:28:57,103
Cool.

345
00:29:03,109 --> 00:29:04,376
Oh.

346
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,145
I'm gonna go see him.
Yeah.

347
00:29:15,988 --> 00:29:17,089
Dad.

348
00:29:17,123 --> 00:29:18,457
(CHUCKLES QUIETLY)

349
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:22,461
Well...

350
00:29:25,464 --> 00:29:27,133
It's gonna be strange,

351
00:29:28,234 --> 00:29:30,236
you not living under my roof.

352
00:29:32,204 --> 00:29:34,206
Yeah.

353
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:36,042
It's gonna be
strange for me, too.

354
00:29:38,377 --> 00:29:40,379
You know it will
always be your home, right?

355
00:29:49,856 --> 00:29:52,024
I love you, Dad. Forever.

356
00:29:59,498 --> 00:30:01,567
I love you, too, Bells.

357
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:04,203
I always have and I always will.

358
00:30:10,442 --> 00:30:11,243
All right.

359
00:30:14,580 --> 00:30:16,015
Go on.

360
00:30:16,048 --> 00:30:18,918
You don't wanna miss your plane.

361
00:30:18,951 --> 00:30:20,319
Wherever it's going.

362
00:30:22,221 --> 00:30:23,923
(LAUGHS)

363
00:30:23,956 --> 00:30:24,891
Okay.

364
00:30:27,426 --> 00:30:28,394
Bye.

365
00:30:34,033 --> 00:30:35,434
You ready?

366
00:30:35,467 --> 00:30:37,203
(GUESTS CHEERING)

367
00:30:56,288 --> 00:30:57,289
Yeah, I'm ready.

368
00:31:09,101 --> 00:31:12,905
(WOLF HOWLING)

369
00:31:44,203 --> 00:31:45,972
(SAMBA MUSIC PLAYING)

370
00:31:53,545 --> 00:31:54,913
(PEOPLE SINGING IN PORTUGUESE)

371
00:32:02,588 --> 00:32:03,489
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

372
00:32:09,728 --> 00:32:11,097
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

373
00:32:45,164 --> 00:32:47,699
So, we're not staying in Rio?

374
00:32:47,733 --> 00:32:49,668
No, we're just passing through.

375
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,304
Are we close?

376
00:33:09,055 --> 00:33:11,123
EDWARD: That's Isle Esme.

377
00:33:11,157 --> 00:33:12,724
It was a gift from Carlisle.

378
00:33:26,138 --> 00:33:27,439
(SQUEALS)

379
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:30,742
Is this totally necessary?

380
00:33:32,078 --> 00:33:34,246
I am nothing if not traditional.

381
00:33:49,128 --> 00:33:51,130
You wanna take a look around?

382
00:34:40,712 --> 00:34:42,080
You tired?

383
00:34:45,284 --> 00:34:46,618
(SIGHING)

384
00:34:48,654 --> 00:34:50,489
Do you wanna go for a swim?

385
00:34:50,522 --> 00:34:52,458
Yeah, that sounds nice.

386
00:35:00,699 --> 00:35:02,634
I could use a few human minutes.

387
00:35:09,575 --> 00:35:10,842
Don't take too long,
Mrs. Cullen.

388
00:35:13,845 --> 00:35:14,746
(SIGHING) Okay.

389
00:35:28,594 --> 00:35:30,562
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

390
00:35:31,797 --> 00:35:32,898
(EXHALING)

391
00:35:36,535 --> 00:35:37,669
Okay.

392
00:35:37,703 --> 00:35:39,838
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

393
00:36:15,006 --> 00:36:15,841
Alice!

394
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:37,563
(EXHALING)

395
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,732
Don't be a coward. (SCOFFS)

396
00:36:53,645 --> 00:36:55,614
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

397
00:37:33,619 --> 00:37:35,387
You're so beautiful.

398
00:37:55,841 --> 00:37:57,343
I promised that we'd try.

399
00:37:59,578 --> 00:38:01,279
If this doesn't work...

400
00:38:02,448 --> 00:38:03,749
I trust you.

401
00:38:11,089 --> 00:38:13,058
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

402
00:38:20,766 --> 00:38:21,833
(GIGGLING)

403
00:38:40,952 --> 00:38:42,654
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

404
00:38:50,562 --> 00:38:51,730
It's okay.

405
00:39:01,873 --> 00:39:03,074
(ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

406
00:40:40,071 --> 00:40:41,006
EDWARD:
How badly are you hurt?

407
00:40:44,142 --> 00:40:45,143
What?

408
00:40:55,621 --> 00:40:56,888
No, Bella, look.

409
00:41:07,533 --> 00:41:09,835
Bella, I can't tell
you how sorry I am.

410
00:41:24,115 --> 00:41:26,251
I'm not.

411
00:41:26,284 --> 00:41:28,186
Really, I'm not.
I'm fine.

412
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:29,888
Don't say you're fine.

413
00:41:31,657 --> 00:41:32,824
Just don't.

414
00:41:33,659 --> 00:41:34,793
No, you don't.

415
00:41:35,861 --> 00:41:36,895
Don't ruin this.

416
00:41:36,928 --> 00:41:37,996
I've already ruined it.

417
00:41:42,167 --> 00:41:44,102
Why can't you see how
perfectly happy I am?

418
00:41:45,937 --> 00:41:47,906
Or was five seconds ago.

419
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:52,243
I mean, now I'm sort
of pissed off, actually.

420
00:41:52,277 --> 00:41:53,945
You should be angry with me.

421
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:57,983
I mean, we knew this was
gonna be tricky, right?

422
00:41:59,117 --> 00:42:01,019
I think we did amazing.

423
00:42:05,156 --> 00:42:06,558
I mean, it was amazing for me.

424
00:42:07,959 --> 00:42:10,061
That's what
you're worried about?

425
00:42:10,095 --> 00:42:11,997
That I didn't enjoy myself?

426
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,803
I know it's not
the same for you,

427
00:42:20,071 --> 00:42:22,007
but for a human, I can't imagine

428
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,675
that it gets any
better than that.

429
00:42:28,013 --> 00:42:30,281
Last night

430
00:42:30,315 --> 00:42:31,983
was the best
night of my existence.

431
00:42:37,122 --> 00:42:38,724
You're the best.

432
00:42:57,308 --> 00:42:58,677
You're not gonna
touch me again, are you?

433
00:43:04,315 --> 00:43:05,617
You know that's not what I mean.

434
00:43:06,718 --> 00:43:08,119
Let me make you breakfast.

435
00:43:16,261 --> 00:43:18,163
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

436
00:43:49,394 --> 00:43:50,729
(LAUGHS)

437
00:43:56,134 --> 00:43:57,635
(EDWARD FAKES SNORING)

438
00:44:14,352 --> 00:44:15,420
(WHOOPS)

439
00:45:22,087 --> 00:45:23,088
I win.

440
00:45:34,332 --> 00:45:36,101
(LAUGHTER ECHOING)

441
00:45:37,969 --> 00:45:39,170
Bella?

442
00:45:43,141 --> 00:45:44,876
You having a nightmare?

443
00:45:45,476 --> 00:45:46,344
No.

444
00:45:54,019 --> 00:45:55,453
(SNIFFLING)

445
00:45:55,486 --> 00:45:57,255
It was just a dream.

446
00:45:59,891 --> 00:46:02,160
It was a really good dream.

447
00:46:02,193 --> 00:46:03,528
Then why are you crying?

448
00:46:05,396 --> 00:46:07,532
Because I wanted it to be real.

449
00:46:09,167 --> 00:46:10,201
Tell me.

450
00:46:16,908 --> 00:46:18,276
Bella, I can't.

451
00:46:21,947 --> 00:46:23,148
Please.

452
00:46:25,851 --> 00:46:26,885
Please.

453
00:47:00,651 --> 00:47:04,189
JACOB: Maybe they'll say
she was in a car crash.

454
00:47:04,222 --> 00:47:06,925
Or tripped and fell off a cliff.

455
00:47:06,958 --> 00:47:08,860
PAUL: Keep it in play!
Keep it in play!

456
00:47:08,894 --> 00:47:10,929
Come on!

457
00:47:10,962 --> 00:47:12,030
(PLAYERS LAUGHING)

458
00:47:12,063 --> 00:47:14,933
Come on! Come on!

459
00:47:14,966 --> 00:47:16,234
At least I'll get
one thing out of it.

460
00:47:18,403 --> 00:47:19,905
No, you won't.

461
00:47:21,639 --> 00:47:25,510
Cullens are not a danger
to the town or the tribe.

462
00:47:25,543 --> 00:47:27,645
Well, he's either gonna
kill her or change her.

463
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:30,115
And the treaty says...
I say, Jacob.

464
00:47:31,349 --> 00:47:32,317
I say.

465
00:47:39,524 --> 00:47:41,893
You know, if you wanted things
different, you should've become alpha.

466
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:48,566
Turning it down seemed
like a good idea at the time.

467
00:47:48,599 --> 00:47:52,170
Jake, you really think you could kill
Bella if she comes back a vampire?

468
00:47:52,203 --> 00:47:54,940
No, make one of us do it,
then hold a grudge against us.

469
00:47:54,973 --> 00:47:56,607
Shut up, Leah.

470
00:47:56,641 --> 00:47:59,444
Would you just get over it? It's
not like you've imprinted on her.

471
00:48:02,513 --> 00:48:03,881
At least they seem happy.

472
00:48:06,651 --> 00:48:08,286
Yeah, some people are
just lucky, I guess.

473
00:48:08,319 --> 00:48:09,320
Lucky?

474
00:48:11,689 --> 00:48:14,392
None of them belong
to themselves anymore.

475
00:48:14,425 --> 00:48:18,363
And the sickest part is their genes
tell them they're happy about it.

476
00:48:20,231 --> 00:48:21,933
Least if you
imprinted on someone,

477
00:48:21,967 --> 00:48:23,401
you'd finally
forget about Bella.

478
00:48:27,205 --> 00:48:30,375
I mean, being any kind of happy
is better than being miserable

479
00:48:30,408 --> 00:48:32,077
about someone you can't have.

480
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:56,534
Pillows survived.

481
00:48:59,604 --> 00:49:01,272
Practice makes perfect, right?

482
00:49:03,241 --> 00:49:05,076
I told you that.

483
00:49:10,048 --> 00:49:12,383
That smells amazing.

484
00:49:12,417 --> 00:49:14,185
(CHUCKLES)
I'm starving.

485
00:49:17,755 --> 00:49:20,291
You realize how many eggs you've
gone through since you've been here?

486
00:49:20,325 --> 00:49:22,427
This island must have messed
with my appetite or something.

487
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:24,129
I'm gonna get fat here.
(LAUGHS)

488
00:49:29,034 --> 00:49:32,237
Eat as many eggs as you like. Pretty
soon you won't want them anymore.

489
00:49:32,270 --> 00:49:37,408
Or cheeseburgers. Or
chocolate. Or ice cream.

490
00:49:37,442 --> 00:49:39,377
Well, maybe
it doesn't have to be

491
00:49:40,578 --> 00:49:42,147
so soon.

492
00:49:44,182 --> 00:49:45,416
Will you wait?

493
00:49:50,688 --> 00:49:53,258
Look, I can't
understand you at all.

494
00:49:53,291 --> 00:49:56,361
Look, I did not know

495
00:49:58,629 --> 00:50:00,765
how good being human could be.

496
00:50:05,636 --> 00:50:06,704
(SIGHS)

497
00:50:06,737 --> 00:50:09,240
So sex was the key after all.

498
00:50:11,509 --> 00:50:13,544
If I'd have known that,

499
00:50:13,578 --> 00:50:15,413
I could have saved
myself a lot of arguments.

500
00:50:16,481 --> 00:50:17,682
Yeah, you probably could have.

501
00:50:32,130 --> 00:50:33,331
Just hold that thought.

502
00:50:40,205 --> 00:50:41,739
(CHATTING QUIETLY)

503
00:50:44,442 --> 00:50:46,577
Bella, these are our
housekeepers, Gustavo and Kaure.

504
00:50:46,611 --> 00:50:47,445
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

505
00:50:54,852 --> 00:50:57,355
Well, I guess we
just leave them to it.

506
00:51:02,260 --> 00:51:03,661
What was that all about?

507
00:51:03,694 --> 00:51:05,496
She's afraid for you.

508
00:51:05,696 --> 00:51:06,764
Why?

509
00:51:08,766 --> 00:51:11,202
Because I have
you here all alone.

510
00:51:13,338 --> 00:51:15,340
You mean she knows about you?

511
00:51:15,373 --> 00:51:18,509
She suspects.

512
00:51:18,543 --> 00:51:21,579
She's native Ticuna. They have
legends about blood-drinking demons

513
00:51:21,612 --> 00:51:24,482
who prey on beautiful women.

514
00:51:28,419 --> 00:51:29,620
(EXCLAIMING IN PORTUGUESE)

515
00:51:30,821 --> 00:51:31,822
Hey.

516
00:51:33,558 --> 00:51:34,559
(LAUGHS)

517
00:52:06,824 --> 00:52:08,226
You're late.

518
00:52:57,242 --> 00:52:58,709
(RETCHING)

519
00:53:06,251 --> 00:53:06,851
Bella?

520
00:53:09,254 --> 00:53:10,821
Hey, don't come in here.

521
00:53:12,557 --> 00:53:15,693
You don't need to see this.

522
00:53:15,726 --> 00:53:17,828
"In sickness and health,"
remember?

523
00:53:19,264 --> 00:53:21,232
It must have been the chicken.

524
00:53:21,266 --> 00:53:22,300
Could you grab my bag?

525
00:53:38,783 --> 00:53:39,584
What is it?

526
00:53:43,854 --> 00:53:46,691
How many days has it been
since the wedding?

527
00:53:46,724 --> 00:53:47,792
Fourteen. Why?

528
00:53:50,895 --> 00:53:52,297
Will you tell me
what's going on?

529
00:53:53,864 --> 00:53:54,665
I'm late.

530
00:53:56,667 --> 00:53:57,935
My period, it's late.

531
00:54:15,453 --> 00:54:16,754
That's impossible.

532
00:54:19,990 --> 00:54:20,825
Can this happen?

533
00:54:28,065 --> 00:54:29,467
Whoa!

534
00:54:29,500 --> 00:54:30,401
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

535
00:54:39,777 --> 00:54:40,911
Alice.
ALICE: Bella?

536
00:54:41,779 --> 00:54:43,814
Are you all right?

537
00:54:43,848 --> 00:54:45,650
I'm not 100% sure.

538
00:54:45,683 --> 00:54:47,952
Why? What's wrong? I just...

539
00:54:47,985 --> 00:54:50,455
You just what?

540
00:54:50,488 --> 00:54:51,456
Alice, what did you see?

541
00:54:51,489 --> 00:54:52,890
Here's Carlisle.

542
00:54:52,923 --> 00:54:54,191
CARLISLE:
Bella, what's going on?

543
00:54:54,224 --> 00:54:57,328
I don't know. I'm a little worried.
Can vampires go into shock?

544
00:54:57,362 --> 00:54:58,629
Has Edward been harmed?

545
00:54:58,663 --> 00:54:59,697
No.

546
00:55:02,400 --> 00:55:06,437
I know that it's impossible,
but I think that I'm pregnant.

547
00:55:08,473 --> 00:55:09,640
Whoa!

548
00:55:13,878 --> 00:55:16,581
Carlisle, I swear, something
just moved inside me.

549
00:55:19,850 --> 00:55:21,118
Is this even possible?

550
00:55:21,151 --> 00:55:22,853
I don't know.

551
00:55:22,887 --> 00:55:24,522
What's he saying?

552
00:55:24,555 --> 00:55:26,657
The sooner Bella's here, the
sooner we can find out what it is.

553
00:55:26,691 --> 00:55:28,058
I need you to get to
the mainland at once.

554
00:55:28,092 --> 00:55:29,827
Yeah, yeah, I will.

555
00:55:34,399 --> 00:55:35,533
Well?

556
00:55:46,577 --> 00:55:47,878
Damn it.

557
00:55:47,912 --> 00:55:49,113
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

558
00:55:49,146 --> 00:55:51,482
Kaure's making sure
you're still alive.

559
00:55:51,516 --> 00:55:53,050
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

560
00:57:01,752 --> 00:57:03,087
(EDWARD AND KAURE ARGUING)

561
00:57:05,823 --> 00:57:06,857
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

562
00:57:19,269 --> 00:57:21,772
What?

563
00:57:21,806 --> 00:57:23,007
Her people have legends.
She might have seen this before.

564
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:23,874
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

565
00:58:29,974 --> 00:58:32,076
I'm not gonna let it hurt you.

566
00:58:35,312 --> 00:58:38,549
Carlisle will
get that thing out.

567
00:58:48,993 --> 00:58:49,960
Thing?

568
00:59:14,251 --> 00:59:16,787
Wait here while we load.

569
00:59:41,779 --> 00:59:42,913
ROSALIE: Hello?

570
00:59:42,947 --> 00:59:44,048
Rosalie.

571
00:59:44,081 --> 00:59:45,049
Bella?

572
00:59:49,153 --> 00:59:50,254
What's going on?

573
00:59:50,287 --> 00:59:51,121
I need your help.

574
01:00:16,881 --> 01:00:18,649
Hey, Son.

575
01:00:18,683 --> 01:00:19,316
What's going on?

576
01:00:20,818 --> 01:00:21,585
Bella called him.

577
01:00:25,255 --> 01:00:27,624
Hey, haven't seen you
in a while.

578
01:00:28,826 --> 01:00:30,094
You okay?

579
01:00:30,127 --> 01:00:30,928
So, you finally
heard from Bella?

580
01:00:34,164 --> 01:00:35,766
They're extending their trip.

581
01:00:35,800 --> 01:00:37,367
Seems she caught a bug.

582
01:00:37,401 --> 01:00:40,037
They wanna wait until she
feels better before they travel.

583
01:00:41,038 --> 01:00:43,007
She's sick.

584
01:00:43,040 --> 01:00:45,676
Yeah, she told me not to
worry, but she sounded,

585
01:00:47,945 --> 01:00:51,315
I don't know, off.

586
01:00:51,348 --> 01:00:52,649
She'll be okay, Charlie.

587
01:00:54,118 --> 01:00:55,219
Come on. Let's eat.

588
01:01:06,964 --> 01:01:09,233
Jacob, let it go.

589
01:01:30,087 --> 01:01:31,221
Is it true?

590
01:01:31,255 --> 01:01:34,058
Hello, Jacob, how are you?

591
01:01:34,091 --> 01:01:36,193
Listen, just
give it to me straight.

592
01:01:36,226 --> 01:01:37,895
BELLA: Jake, is that you?

593
01:01:39,964 --> 01:01:42,399
She's here? They came
home two weeks ago.

594
01:01:43,333 --> 01:01:44,301
Jake.

595
01:02:04,789 --> 01:02:06,323
BELLA: I'm glad you came.

596
01:02:09,026 --> 01:02:11,095
Close enough.
What's your problem?

597
01:02:12,229 --> 01:02:13,998
BELLA: Rose, it's okay.

598
01:02:23,007 --> 01:02:24,975
(SIGHS)

599
01:02:25,009 --> 01:02:26,143
You look terrible.

600
01:02:29,346 --> 01:02:32,149
Yeah, it's nice to see you, too.

601
01:02:36,420 --> 01:02:37,955
So, are you gonna tell me
what's wrong with you?

602
01:02:41,291 --> 01:02:42,827
Rose, you wanna help me up?

603
01:03:02,146 --> 01:03:03,814
You did this!

604
01:03:03,848 --> 01:03:06,917
We didn't know it
was even possible.

605
01:03:06,951 --> 01:03:08,552
What is it?
CARLISLE: I'm not sure.

606
01:03:08,585 --> 01:03:11,455
Ultrasounds and needles won't
penetrate the embryonic sac.

607
01:03:11,488 --> 01:03:13,223
I can't see it, either.

608
01:03:15,492 --> 01:03:18,829
And I can't see
Bella's future anymore.

609
01:03:18,863 --> 01:03:21,265
CARLISLE: We've been researching
legends, but there isn't much to go on.

610
01:03:21,298 --> 01:03:23,200
What we do know is
that it's strong.

611
01:03:23,233 --> 01:03:24,568
And fast-growing.

612
01:03:24,601 --> 01:03:28,005
Why haven't you done
anything? Take it out of her!

613
01:03:28,038 --> 01:03:29,874
This is none of
your business, dog.

614
01:03:29,907 --> 01:03:31,441
Rose!

615
01:03:31,475 --> 01:03:33,277
All this fighting
isn't good for Bella.

616
01:03:33,310 --> 01:03:35,479
The fetus isn't good for Bella.

617
01:03:35,512 --> 01:03:40,150
Say the word, Alice. "Baby."
It's just a little baby.

618
01:03:40,184 --> 01:03:42,086
Carlisle, you've gotta
do something.

619
01:03:42,119 --> 01:03:44,521
No.

620
01:03:44,554 --> 01:03:46,924
It's not his decision.
It's not any of yours.

621
01:03:46,957 --> 01:03:48,292
Jacob, I need to talk to you.

622
01:04:00,270 --> 01:04:02,206
I always knew you'd destroy her.

623
01:04:05,275 --> 01:04:08,612
She thinks Carlisle can
turn her at the last minute,

624
01:04:08,645 --> 01:04:10,447
like he did for me and Esme.

625
01:04:10,480 --> 01:04:15,252
Can he?
Probability is slight.

626
01:04:18,155 --> 01:04:20,124
And if her heart fails...

627
01:04:27,064 --> 01:04:28,999
Look, Jacob, I need you
to do something for me.

628
01:04:29,033 --> 01:04:30,167
(SCOFFS)

629
01:04:30,935 --> 01:04:32,202
For her.

630
01:04:36,006 --> 01:04:40,277
You have a connection with her
that I'll never understand.

631
01:04:40,310 --> 01:04:42,913
Maybe you could talk to her,
change her mind.

632
01:04:46,050 --> 01:04:48,052
You can keep her alive.

633
01:04:49,619 --> 01:04:51,421
And if I can't?

634
01:04:52,957 --> 01:04:54,424
If she dies,

635
01:04:59,163 --> 01:05:01,431
you get what you always wanted.

636
01:05:02,632 --> 01:05:03,968
To kill me.

637
01:05:15,212 --> 01:05:17,147
Rose, I'm fine, really.

638
01:05:37,501 --> 01:05:40,437
So, Edward sent you in
here to talk to me? Sort of.

639
01:05:40,470 --> 01:05:43,440
Though I can't figure out why
he thinks you'd listen to me.

640
01:05:43,473 --> 01:05:45,042
I mean, you never have before.

641
01:05:45,075 --> 01:05:46,243
(BOTH LAUGH)

642
01:05:53,550 --> 01:05:55,285
Since when are you
and blondie BFFs?

643
01:05:55,319 --> 01:05:57,354
Rose understands what I want.

644
01:06:02,692 --> 01:06:04,728
What are you thinking, Bella?

645
01:06:05,529 --> 01:06:06,630
Seriously.

646
01:06:06,663 --> 01:06:09,466
I know this seems
like a scary thing,

647
01:06:11,068 --> 01:06:12,436
but it's not.

648
01:06:14,071 --> 01:06:16,006
It's like this
miracle or something.

649
01:06:17,807 --> 01:06:19,009
I can feel him.

650
01:06:19,043 --> 01:06:20,477
(SCOFFS)

651
01:06:20,510 --> 01:06:23,447
So, it's a bouncing baby boy.

652
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:25,749
I'm sorry I didn't know. Should've
brought some blue balloons.

653
01:06:25,782 --> 01:06:28,518
It's just a guess.

654
01:06:28,552 --> 01:06:30,687
When I picture him, I see a boy.

655
01:06:33,123 --> 01:06:33,757
We'll see.

656
01:06:35,192 --> 01:06:37,161
You won't.

657
01:06:37,194 --> 01:06:38,562
Jake, I can do this.

658
01:06:40,264 --> 01:06:41,465
I'm strong enough.

659
01:06:41,498 --> 01:06:44,268
Come on.

660
01:06:44,301 --> 01:06:48,572
You can spout that crap to your
bloodsucker, but you don't fool me.

661
01:06:48,605 --> 01:06:52,042
I can see what that thing's
doing to you. It's a killer, Bella.

662
01:06:52,709 --> 01:06:54,111
You're wrong.

663
01:06:54,144 --> 01:06:55,779
And when you die,

664
01:06:55,812 --> 01:07:00,450
what was the point? Of me
loving you, you loving him.

665
01:07:00,484 --> 01:07:02,486
How is that right for anyone?

666
01:07:02,519 --> 01:07:04,088
Because I sure don't see it.

667
01:07:13,463 --> 01:07:14,531
Listen to me, Bella.

668
01:07:14,564 --> 01:07:15,599
Please.

669
01:07:16,700 --> 01:07:18,668
Just don't do this.

670
01:07:20,104 --> 01:07:22,606
Live, okay?

671
01:07:22,639 --> 01:07:24,808
Please.

672
01:07:24,841 --> 01:07:27,777
Jake, everything's
gonna be okay.

673
01:07:40,790 --> 01:07:42,092
Jacob, don't go.

674
01:07:43,360 --> 01:07:44,761
I know how this ends.

675
01:07:47,564 --> 01:07:49,766
And I'm not
sticking around to watch.

676
01:08:08,485 --> 01:08:10,454
(GROANS)

677
01:08:18,262 --> 01:08:19,463
(GROWLING)

678
01:08:27,237 --> 01:08:29,639
BELLA: Jacob. Jake, I
can do this. I can do this.

679
01:08:30,540 --> 01:08:32,476
JACOB: Don't do this.

680
01:08:32,509 --> 01:08:33,677
BELLA: I'm strong enough.
I'm strong enough.

681
01:08:33,710 --> 01:08:35,712
ROSALIE: This is none
of your business, dog.

682
01:08:35,745 --> 01:08:38,215
BELLA: Jacob, don't go.

683
01:08:38,248 --> 01:08:39,783
JACOB: You did this!

684
01:08:39,816 --> 01:08:41,418
Everything's gonna be okay.

685
01:08:41,451 --> 01:08:43,587
ALICE: The fetus
isn't good for Bella.

686
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:46,156
JACOB: I know how this ends.

687
01:08:46,190 --> 01:08:48,392
Don't you even care
that it's killing you?

688
01:08:58,635 --> 01:08:59,903
(HOWLING)

689
01:09:03,573 --> 01:09:04,841
(HOWLING)

690
01:09:14,218 --> 01:09:15,685
(WOLVES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

691
01:09:15,719 --> 01:09:17,354
(GROWLING)

692
01:09:27,597 --> 01:09:29,899
WOLVES: Jake! Jake! Jake!

693
01:09:29,933 --> 01:09:31,668
Jake! Jake! Jake!

694
01:09:34,871 --> 01:09:36,340
PAUL: Is it true, Jacob?
QUIL: What will it be?

695
01:09:36,373 --> 01:09:37,407
PAUL: It's growing fast.

696
01:09:37,441 --> 01:09:38,508
LEAH: It's unnatural.
JARED: Dangerous.

697
01:09:38,542 --> 01:09:40,910
QUIL: Monstrosity.
PAUL: An abomination.

698
01:09:40,944 --> 01:09:43,380
QUIL: On our land.

699
01:09:43,413 --> 01:09:44,981
JARED: We can't allow it.
QUIL: We can't allow it.

700
01:09:45,014 --> 01:09:46,716
PAUL: We can't allow it.

701
01:09:46,750 --> 01:09:47,984
WOLVES: We can't allow it.

702
01:09:48,017 --> 01:09:50,287
SAM: We have to
protect the tribe.

703
01:09:50,320 --> 01:09:53,823
What they've bred won't
be able to control its thirst.

704
01:09:53,857 --> 01:09:56,226
Every human will be in danger.

705
01:09:56,260 --> 01:09:58,395
JARED: We're ready.
LEAH: No time to waste.

706
01:09:58,428 --> 01:09:59,829
JACOB: Now?

707
01:09:59,863 --> 01:10:02,532
SAM: We must destroy
it before it's born.

708
01:10:02,566 --> 01:10:04,234
SETH: You mean, kill Bella?

709
01:10:04,268 --> 01:10:06,970
SAM: Her choice
affects us all.

710
01:10:07,003 --> 01:10:10,340
JACOB: Bella's human.
Our protection applies to her.

711
01:10:10,374 --> 01:10:12,342
LEAH: She's dying anyway!

712
01:10:12,376 --> 01:10:13,610
(BOTH GROWLING)

713
01:10:16,713 --> 01:10:18,848
SAM: We have real
enemies to fight tonight.

714
01:10:18,882 --> 01:10:20,284
JACOB: Tonight?

715
01:10:22,552 --> 01:10:25,389
SAM: You will
fight with us, Jake.

716
01:10:28,392 --> 01:10:29,926
(GROWLING)

717
01:10:29,959 --> 01:10:31,428
(GROWLING)

718
01:10:34,798 --> 01:10:36,600
(BOTH SNARLING)

719
01:10:45,074 --> 01:10:50,280
JACOB: (STRAINING) I will not.

720
01:10:50,314 --> 01:10:54,418
I am the grandson
of Ephraim Black.

721
01:10:54,451 --> 01:10:58,522
I am the grandson of a chief!

722
01:10:58,555 --> 01:11:02,359
I wasn't born to
follow you, or anyone else.

723
01:11:02,392 --> 01:11:03,760
(GROWLING)

724
01:11:33,757 --> 01:11:35,359
(TWIG SNAPS)

725
01:11:35,392 --> 01:11:36,025
Whoa.

726
01:11:40,063 --> 01:11:42,065
Don't worry.
They're not following us.

727
01:11:42,098 --> 01:11:43,867
What do you think
you're doing here?

728
01:11:43,900 --> 01:11:45,835
I left Sam's pack.
Go home, Seth.

729
01:11:45,869 --> 01:11:47,070
I won't stand behind him.

730
01:11:47,103 --> 01:11:48,872
Oh, yes, you will.

731
01:11:48,905 --> 01:11:51,341
I'm not kidding.
Get out of here.

732
01:11:53,076 --> 01:11:56,613
Is that an order?
Gonna make me bow down, too?

733
01:11:56,646 --> 01:11:59,883
I'm not ordering anyone.

734
01:11:59,916 --> 01:12:02,051
Look, I'm just going off
on my own here, okay?

735
01:12:02,085 --> 01:12:04,388
Great, and I've got your back.

736
01:12:04,421 --> 01:12:05,555
No, you don't.

737
01:12:08,725 --> 01:12:10,927
If Sam comes after Bella,

738
01:12:10,960 --> 01:12:14,030
are you really ready
to fight your own brothers?

739
01:12:14,063 --> 01:12:15,331
Your sister?

740
01:12:16,633 --> 01:12:18,802
If it's the right thing to do.

741
01:12:22,606 --> 01:12:23,740
Whatever.

742
01:12:24,974 --> 01:12:27,877
I'm gonna go give
the Cullens a heads-up.

743
01:12:27,911 --> 01:12:29,613
Do what you want.

744
01:12:33,750 --> 01:12:38,588
How cool is this? Two-man
pack. Two against the world.

745
01:12:38,622 --> 01:12:40,457
You're getting on
my nerves, Seth.

746
01:12:40,490 --> 01:12:42,859
I'll shut up. Can do.

747
01:12:47,531 --> 01:12:49,633
Get ready.

748
01:12:49,666 --> 01:12:51,568
They're coming for Bella.

749
01:12:54,037 --> 01:12:55,705
They're not gonna touch her.

750
01:12:55,739 --> 01:12:56,773
Agreed.

751
01:13:03,580 --> 01:13:06,616
Man, I can smell them
from all the way out here.

752
01:13:06,650 --> 01:13:08,418
What the hell
are you doing here?

753
01:13:08,452 --> 01:13:10,019
I'm not gonna let my little
brother get himself killed.

754
01:13:10,053 --> 01:13:12,689
Go away, Leah!
I can take care of myself.

755
01:13:12,722 --> 01:13:14,991
That you think so
proves you need a babysitter.

756
01:13:15,024 --> 01:13:15,859
Okay, would
the both of you shut up?

757
01:13:19,095 --> 01:13:20,497
Did Sam send you?

758
01:13:20,530 --> 01:13:22,432
Sam doesn't even know I left.

759
01:13:22,466 --> 01:13:23,867
(WOLVES HOWLING)

760
01:13:27,203 --> 01:13:29,506
I think he just figured it out.

761
01:13:30,840 --> 01:13:31,841
Jake.

762
01:13:33,577 --> 01:13:34,878
I know what his plan is.

763
01:13:36,580 --> 01:13:38,582
Sam's lost
the element of surprise,

764
01:13:38,615 --> 01:13:40,584
and he doesn't want
to take you on outnumbered,

765
01:13:40,617 --> 01:13:42,452
so he's not gonna
come at you head on.

766
01:13:42,486 --> 01:13:45,522
He's got the place surrounded
and he'll wait for his opportunity.

767
01:13:45,555 --> 01:13:46,590
We won't get
through without a fight.

768
01:13:46,623 --> 01:13:48,792
No fights.

769
01:13:48,825 --> 01:13:49,993
We won't be the ones
to break the treaty.

770
01:13:50,026 --> 01:13:53,162
The treaty is void,
at least in Sam's mind.

771
01:13:53,196 --> 01:13:54,798
Not in ours.

772
01:13:54,831 --> 01:13:57,567
Carlisle,
no one's hunted for weeks.

773
01:13:59,202 --> 01:14:01,738
We'll make do.

774
01:14:04,107 --> 01:14:05,609
You've done us
a great service, Jacob.

775
01:14:05,642 --> 01:14:06,910
Thank you.

776
01:14:09,012 --> 01:14:10,914
(WOLVES APPROACHING)

777
01:14:10,947 --> 01:14:12,882
(GROWLING)

778
01:14:17,153 --> 01:14:18,788
(GROWLING)

779
01:14:38,107 --> 01:14:42,646
I know they're out there somewhere,
but I can't hear them anymore.

780
01:14:44,180 --> 01:14:45,915
It's so quiet.

781
01:14:47,684 --> 01:14:50,854
I stopped hearing them, too,
the second I decided to leave.

782
01:14:52,622 --> 01:14:54,691
It's nice.

783
01:14:56,793 --> 01:14:58,728
You know you can't stay here.

784
01:14:58,762 --> 01:15:00,830
But I don't have any place... I
can't trust you with the Cullens.

785
01:15:00,864 --> 01:15:02,832
You hate them too much.

786
01:15:03,900 --> 01:15:04,968
You don't even like me.

787
01:15:05,001 --> 01:15:06,703
I don't have to.

788
01:15:08,271 --> 01:15:11,708
I just have to follow you.

789
01:15:11,741 --> 01:15:15,545
Look, Seth doesn't want
you here. Neither do I.

790
01:15:19,616 --> 01:15:22,185
Being unwanted isn't exactly
a new thing for me.

791
01:15:38,802 --> 01:15:41,104
Look, I'll stay out of your way.

792
01:15:41,137 --> 01:15:42,806
I'll do whatever you want,

793
01:15:42,839 --> 01:15:44,608
except go back to Sam's pack

794
01:15:44,641 --> 01:15:46,976
and be the pathetic ex-girlfriend
he can't get away from.

795
01:15:48,978 --> 01:15:52,616
You don't know how many times I
wished I could imprint on someone.

796
01:15:53,382 --> 01:15:54,250
Anyone.

797
01:15:57,253 --> 01:15:59,088
Just to break the connection.

798
01:16:12,802 --> 01:16:14,037
(SIGHS)

799
01:16:14,070 --> 01:16:15,104
All right.

800
01:16:17,674 --> 01:16:20,644
I'm gonna do a perimeter run.
You got my flank?

801
01:17:02,819 --> 01:17:04,821
Rosalie, why don't you get
Jacob something from the kitchen?

802
01:17:05,955 --> 01:17:08,157
Thanks, but no thanks.

803
01:17:08,191 --> 01:17:12,261
I'd rather not eat something
with blondie's spit in it.

804
01:17:12,295 --> 01:17:14,297
She would never embarrass
me with such a lack of hospitality.

805
01:17:15,031 --> 01:17:16,032
Hmm.

806
01:17:18,735 --> 01:17:19,869
Of course not.

807
01:17:26,843 --> 01:17:28,044
You'd tell me if she
poisoned it, right?

808
01:17:36,953 --> 01:17:38,154
He broke another
one of her ribs.

809
01:17:39,188 --> 01:17:42,125
(POTS CLATTERING)

810
01:17:54,003 --> 01:17:55,038
Enjoy it, mongrel.

811
01:18:00,409 --> 01:18:02,846
And don't make such
a big deal out of it.

812
01:18:02,879 --> 01:18:05,081
Even normal human babies
have been known to crack ribs.

813
01:18:16,960 --> 01:18:17,961
(LAUGHING)

814
01:18:25,401 --> 01:18:29,405
You got food in my hair.

815
01:18:37,847 --> 01:18:39,215
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

816
01:18:54,130 --> 01:18:55,031
(BABIES CRYING)
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

817
01:19:27,496 --> 01:19:28,531
CARLISLE: Your rib is cracked.

818
01:19:30,867 --> 01:19:34,103
But there are no splinters.
You haven't punctured anything.

819
01:19:34,137 --> 01:19:35,238
Yet.

820
01:19:35,271 --> 01:19:36,305
Edward.

821
01:19:38,441 --> 01:19:42,178
It's breaking her bones now.

822
01:19:42,211 --> 01:19:43,847
It's crushing you
from the inside out.

823
01:19:45,915 --> 01:19:49,418
Carlisle, tell her what
you told me. Tell her.

824
01:19:52,455 --> 01:19:55,058
Carlisle, tell me.
It's all right.

825
01:20:06,369 --> 01:20:08,004
The fetus isn't
compatible with your body.

826
01:20:10,907 --> 01:20:12,909
It's too strong.

827
01:20:12,942 --> 01:20:15,945
It won't allow you to get
the nutrition you need.

828
01:20:15,979 --> 01:20:17,380
It's starving you by the hour.

829
01:20:17,413 --> 01:20:19,282
I can't stop it,
and I can't slow it down.

830
01:20:22,919 --> 01:20:25,288
At this rate, your heart will
give out before you can deliver.

831
01:20:30,593 --> 01:20:31,928
Then I'll hold on as
long as I can, and then...

832
01:20:31,961 --> 01:20:34,163
Bella.

833
01:20:34,197 --> 01:20:36,365
There are some conditions
that even venom can't overcome.

834
01:20:38,034 --> 01:20:38,868
You understand?

835
01:20:40,536 --> 01:20:41,604
I'm sorry.

836
01:20:54,517 --> 01:20:57,153
Edward, I'm sorry.

837
01:20:57,186 --> 01:20:59,588
I can't live without you.

838
01:20:59,622 --> 01:21:02,125
You won't. You're
gonna have a part of me.

839
01:21:02,158 --> 01:21:04,227
He'll need you.

840
01:21:04,260 --> 01:21:07,563
Do you honestly think
that I could love it

841
01:21:07,596 --> 01:21:10,666
or even tolerate
it if it killed you?

842
01:21:10,699 --> 01:21:12,068
It's not his fault.

843
01:21:13,336 --> 01:21:15,238
You have to accept what is.

844
01:21:15,271 --> 01:21:18,107
Because you've
given me no choice!

845
01:21:18,141 --> 01:21:21,544
Bella, we're supposed to
be partners, remember?

846
01:21:21,577 --> 01:21:23,980
But you decided
this on your own.

847
01:21:24,013 --> 01:21:25,581
You've decided to leave me.

848
01:21:25,614 --> 01:21:27,316
Don't see it that way.

849
01:21:27,350 --> 01:21:29,152
Well, I have no
other way to see it.

850
01:21:29,185 --> 01:21:30,319
'Cause it's me who'll lose you.

851
01:21:31,120 --> 01:21:32,255
And I don't choose that.

852
01:21:34,323 --> 01:21:35,891
I don't choose that.

853
01:21:44,700 --> 01:21:45,501
(SIGHS)

854
01:21:48,471 --> 01:21:49,405
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

855
01:22:30,479 --> 01:22:32,581
COMMENTATOR: Washington
driving in the red zone.

856
01:22:32,615 --> 01:22:34,450
Almost stripped of the ball.
He stood up and Calvin finally...

857
01:22:37,453 --> 01:22:38,587
Are you cold?

858
01:22:39,488 --> 01:22:40,623
I got it.

859
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:49,332
Don't do that.

860
01:22:51,034 --> 01:22:52,635
What?

861
01:22:52,668 --> 01:22:55,371
Smile like I'm your
favorite person in the world.

862
01:22:56,272 --> 01:22:57,573
You're one of them.

863
01:23:00,409 --> 01:23:02,578
Feels complete when
you're here, Jake.

864
01:23:07,616 --> 01:23:08,517
(BELLA GASPS)

865
01:23:12,321 --> 01:23:13,622
(WHIMPERS)

866
01:23:17,393 --> 01:23:20,396
We need to find a way to
get some food into her system.

867
01:23:22,598 --> 01:23:25,134
If I could only see
the fetus... The baby.

868
01:23:25,168 --> 01:23:27,070
...maybe I could
figure out what it wants.

869
01:23:35,111 --> 01:23:37,246
Think you might be right.

870
01:23:37,280 --> 01:23:38,414
Jacob just had an idea.

871
01:23:40,816 --> 01:23:44,287
It wasn't an idea.
It was a snide comment.

872
01:23:44,320 --> 01:23:46,222
What were you thinking?

873
01:23:46,255 --> 01:23:49,325
That it's probably just looking
for someone to sink its teeth into.

874
01:24:00,103 --> 01:24:01,237
He's thirsty.

875
01:24:04,207 --> 01:24:07,143
I know the feeling.

876
01:24:07,176 --> 01:24:09,645
If it's craving, it's not
gonna want animal blood.

877
01:24:09,678 --> 01:24:11,414
I have some O negative
laid aside for Bella.

878
01:24:14,250 --> 01:24:15,518
Walk with me.

879
01:24:36,572 --> 01:24:37,806
JACOB: Wait, wait, wait.

880
01:24:37,840 --> 01:24:39,875
You're gonna
make her drink that?

881
01:24:39,908 --> 01:24:42,878
It's the fastest way
to test the theory.

882
01:24:42,911 --> 01:24:44,780
Only if you're
comfortable with it.

883
01:24:44,813 --> 01:24:46,482
I'll try anything.

884
01:24:47,916 --> 01:24:49,385
Just hold on.

885
01:24:50,853 --> 01:24:52,755
I think I'm gonna be sick.

886
01:25:01,397 --> 01:25:03,098
This might make it
a little easier to take.

887
01:25:33,796 --> 01:25:35,198
Tastes

888
01:25:38,734 --> 01:25:39,568
good.

889
01:25:51,814 --> 01:25:53,516
Mmm.

890
01:26:08,597 --> 01:26:10,599
Your pulse is
already getting stronger.

891
01:26:12,435 --> 01:26:13,602
It's working.

892
01:26:19,675 --> 01:26:20,943
(DISTANT HOWLING)

893
01:26:23,779 --> 01:26:25,248
Chatty, aren't they?

894
01:26:26,949 --> 01:26:28,717
Just trying to keep us on edge.

895
01:26:28,751 --> 01:26:29,652
It's working.

896
01:26:36,759 --> 01:26:38,661
What?

897
01:26:38,694 --> 01:26:40,829
I can't just stand next to you?

898
01:26:43,499 --> 01:26:46,435
Okay.

899
01:26:46,469 --> 01:26:51,474
See, when I'm close to you, it's
like being able to shut my eyes.

900
01:26:51,507 --> 01:26:52,641
Everything goes away.

901
01:26:54,677 --> 01:26:56,545
Except for the wet dog smell.

902
01:26:59,948 --> 01:27:01,750
Well, I'm glad
I can help someone.

903
01:27:28,444 --> 01:27:29,378
Well, you sound better.

904
01:27:29,412 --> 01:27:30,779
BELLA: I am.

905
01:27:30,813 --> 01:27:32,348
I feel much better.

906
01:27:32,381 --> 01:27:34,983
This whole thing must've put
a kink in the honeymoon, huh?

907
01:27:36,785 --> 01:27:37,920
You could say that.

908
01:27:37,953 --> 01:27:41,324
Otherwise, married
life treating you okay?

909
01:27:41,357 --> 01:27:44,327
Edward still walks
on water and all that?

910
01:27:44,360 --> 01:27:47,896
Yeah, but, I mean,
it is different now.

911
01:27:47,930 --> 01:27:49,532
The important thing
is that you're better.

912
01:27:49,565 --> 01:27:52,034
And that you're
coming home soon, right?

913
01:27:52,067 --> 01:27:54,503
Okay, Dad, I don't
want you to freak out,

914
01:27:58,574 --> 01:28:00,543
but I'm going to a medical
center in Switzerland.

915
01:28:00,576 --> 01:28:03,045
What? No, no, you're not.
You're not going to Switzerland.

916
01:28:03,078 --> 01:28:04,347
What are you...
You said you were better.

917
01:28:04,380 --> 01:28:06,014
I am.

918
01:28:06,048 --> 01:28:08,417
No, Bella.
I'm getting on a plane. No.

919
01:28:08,451 --> 01:28:09,485
No.

920
01:28:10,619 --> 01:28:15,324
It's really more of a spa.

921
01:28:15,358 --> 01:28:18,461
And I'm sure that I'd be better
by the time you got there anyway.

922
01:28:18,494 --> 01:28:20,663
Bells... I don't know.

923
01:28:20,696 --> 01:28:22,565
Dad, don't come.

924
01:28:22,598 --> 01:28:24,667
And picture me healthy,

925
01:28:24,700 --> 01:28:27,436
like I'm sitting on the couch with
you, eating pizza or something.

926
01:28:27,470 --> 01:28:29,538
You want me to visualize?

927
01:28:29,572 --> 01:28:30,506
They say that it helps.

928
01:28:31,607 --> 01:28:33,476
Just picture me like that.

929
01:28:35,511 --> 01:28:36,912
Like I was.

930
01:28:36,945 --> 01:28:38,814
It'll make me feel better.

931
01:28:40,583 --> 01:28:42,084
Dad, I got to go, okay?

932
01:28:42,117 --> 01:28:43,085
Bella.

933
01:28:43,886 --> 01:28:44,953
I love you.

934
01:28:44,987 --> 01:28:46,355
Bella...

935
01:28:50,659 --> 01:28:51,694
(BREATH TREMBLING)

936
01:29:06,709 --> 01:29:08,777
I'm sorry I've been so angry.

937
01:29:08,811 --> 01:29:10,045
(SNIFFLING)

938
01:29:10,078 --> 01:29:12,481
I would be, too.

939
01:29:12,515 --> 01:29:14,550
I've left you alone in this.

940
01:29:20,489 --> 01:29:21,757
Marriage.

941
01:29:27,496 --> 01:29:29,398
Well, they say the
first year is the hardest.

942
01:29:35,103 --> 01:29:36,739
Who was that?

943
01:29:36,772 --> 01:29:38,006
What?

944
01:29:38,040 --> 01:29:39,542
I thought I just heard...

945
01:29:40,809 --> 01:29:42,445
Just say something else.

946
01:29:43,211 --> 01:29:44,847
Like what?

947
01:29:46,449 --> 01:29:47,683
(LAUGHS)

948
01:29:48,651 --> 01:29:49,685
Edward, what's going on?

949
01:29:52,488 --> 01:29:53,889
He likes the sound
of your voice.

950
01:29:53,922 --> 01:29:55,658
You can hear him?

951
01:29:56,158 --> 01:29:57,426
In mind.

952
01:30:00,796 --> 01:30:03,432
He likes my voice as well.

953
01:30:03,466 --> 01:30:04,567
What?

954
01:30:05,701 --> 01:30:06,935
What do you hear?

955
01:30:06,969 --> 01:30:09,538
It's so strange.

956
01:30:09,572 --> 01:30:12,808
I thought he was like me,
but he's not. He's like you.

957
01:30:12,841 --> 01:30:15,644
Good and pure.

958
01:30:16,545 --> 01:30:17,813
He's happy.

959
01:30:20,649 --> 01:30:23,018
Of course you are.

960
01:30:23,051 --> 01:30:25,554
Of course you're happy.
How could you not be?

961
01:30:26,522 --> 01:30:28,791
I love you so much.

962
01:30:30,793 --> 01:30:32,828
What do you hear now?

963
01:30:32,861 --> 01:30:34,463
He loves you, Bella.

964
01:30:36,632 --> 01:30:38,000
Oh, my gosh.

965
01:31:06,161 --> 01:31:08,096
(EDWARD AND BELLA CHUCKLING)

966
01:31:11,900 --> 01:31:13,135
Jacob.

967
01:31:23,278 --> 01:31:24,947
So, that's the last of it?

968
01:31:24,980 --> 01:31:27,015
Bella could deliver
as early as tomorrow.

969
01:31:27,049 --> 01:31:29,051
If she's going to have any chance
at all, she'll need more blood.

970
01:31:29,084 --> 01:31:30,786
And you need to feed.

971
01:31:30,819 --> 01:31:33,822
You have to be at your strongest
for her. We need to go tonight.

972
01:31:33,856 --> 01:31:36,158
Carlisle, you're the enemy now.

973
01:31:36,191 --> 01:31:38,961
Sam won't hesitate.
You will be slaughtered.

974
01:31:38,994 --> 01:31:40,663
Emmett will come with us.

975
01:31:40,696 --> 01:31:42,130
That won't be enough.

976
01:31:42,164 --> 01:31:43,899
CARLISLE:
We have no choice, Jacob.

977
01:31:43,932 --> 01:31:45,801
If there's anything we can
do to save her, we have to try.

978
01:31:45,834 --> 01:31:47,636
You'd risk your lives for her?

979
01:31:47,670 --> 01:31:49,638
Of course we would.

980
01:31:49,672 --> 01:31:50,973
Bella's a part
of our family now.

981
01:31:53,008 --> 01:31:53,909
Yeah.

982
01:31:55,343 --> 01:31:56,879
I can see that.

983
01:31:58,581 --> 01:31:59,948
This really is a family.

984
01:32:03,852 --> 01:32:06,221
As strong as
the one I was born into.

985
01:32:09,191 --> 01:32:10,593
I know what I have to do.

986
01:32:32,347 --> 01:32:34,116
SETH: Jake! They're coming.

987
01:32:34,149 --> 01:32:35,350
I know.

988
01:32:35,383 --> 01:32:38,086
We should phase, Jacob. We
can't protect ourselves like this.

989
01:32:38,120 --> 01:32:40,689
They'll see it as a threat.

990
01:32:40,723 --> 01:32:42,991
I wanna talk!

991
01:32:43,025 --> 01:32:44,693
Be easier if I
could hear you, too.

992
01:32:52,768 --> 01:32:54,269
(SPITS)

993
01:32:54,302 --> 01:32:55,704
This isn't your
territory anymore.

994
01:32:57,105 --> 01:32:58,240
How's the new
family working out?

995
01:32:58,273 --> 01:32:59,341
You done?

996
01:33:01,644 --> 01:33:02,745
You coming home, Jake?

997
01:33:04,112 --> 01:33:05,614
Not until I finish this.

998
01:33:05,648 --> 01:33:07,015
What do you mean?

999
01:33:07,049 --> 01:33:09,151
I want Sam to take
back Leah and Seth.

1000
01:33:09,184 --> 01:33:10,919
LEAH: What?
SETH: No way!

1001
01:33:10,953 --> 01:33:11,987
Quiet!

1002
01:33:14,422 --> 01:33:15,590
I want them safe.

1003
01:33:16,358 --> 01:33:18,093
And I want this over.

1004
01:33:19,862 --> 01:33:21,296
(GROWLING)

1005
01:33:29,304 --> 01:33:32,307
I need Sam to wait until Bella's
been separated from the problem.

1006
01:33:32,340 --> 01:33:33,842
You mean till she's dead.

1007
01:33:33,876 --> 01:33:34,743
Ease up, Paul.

1008
01:33:36,178 --> 01:33:38,080
Then what?

1009
01:33:38,113 --> 01:33:42,217
Tell Sam that when the moment
comes, I'll be the one to destroy it.

1010
01:33:42,250 --> 01:33:43,285
Jake!

1011
01:33:44,920 --> 01:33:46,755
I'm the only one who can.

1012
01:33:47,856 --> 01:33:49,091
They trust me.

1013
01:33:51,860 --> 01:33:53,128
(RUNNING)

1014
01:33:53,161 --> 01:33:54,329
(ESME PANTING)

1015
01:33:57,733 --> 01:33:58,867
(GROWLING)

1016
01:33:58,901 --> 01:34:01,369
(ESME STRUGGLING)

1017
01:34:09,778 --> 01:34:11,947
(GROWLING)

1018
01:34:16,451 --> 01:34:17,352
(EMMETT GRUNTS)
(DOG WHIMPERS)

1019
01:34:34,069 --> 01:34:36,371
(HOWLING)

1020
01:34:46,849 --> 01:34:48,083
You played us?

1021
01:35:03,866 --> 01:35:05,801
Can't we come up with
something just a little more classic?

1022
01:35:10,005 --> 01:35:12,374
Thank you.

1023
01:35:12,407 --> 01:35:14,309
They make it out all right?
Yeah.

1024
01:35:14,342 --> 01:35:15,443
Good.

1025
01:35:25,187 --> 01:35:26,254
Hey.

1026
01:35:28,356 --> 01:35:30,325
Are you okay?

1027
01:35:30,358 --> 01:35:33,028
Yeah, it's not like I'm
the one carrying a demon.

1028
01:35:33,061 --> 01:35:35,430
This is pretty important, Bella.

1029
01:35:35,463 --> 01:35:37,933
Why don't you tell Jacob
what you've decided?

1030
01:35:37,966 --> 01:35:38,867
What now?

1031
01:35:40,969 --> 01:35:43,205
Rose is trying to talk Bella
out of her baby names.

1032
01:35:43,839 --> 01:35:45,473
She hates them.

1033
01:35:45,507 --> 01:35:47,876
Well, then I'm on your side
no matter what you picked.

1034
01:35:49,144 --> 01:35:50,412
They're not that bad.

1035
01:35:50,445 --> 01:35:52,114
If it's a boy, EJ.

1036
01:35:53,916 --> 01:35:54,950
Edward Jacob.

1037
01:35:57,519 --> 01:36:01,389
Okay, fine,
that one's not awful.

1038
01:36:01,423 --> 01:36:05,027
Why don't you tell
him the girl's name?

1039
01:36:05,060 --> 01:36:07,863
I was playing around
with our moms' names.

1040
01:36:08,496 --> 01:36:10,065
Renee and Esme.

1041
01:36:10,098 --> 01:36:11,233
And I was thinking...

1042
01:36:12,334 --> 01:36:13,468
Renesmee.

1043
01:36:18,506 --> 01:36:19,842
Renesmee.

1044
01:36:19,875 --> 01:36:21,243
(LAUGHING)

1045
01:36:23,545 --> 01:36:24,880
Too weird?

1046
01:36:27,215 --> 01:36:28,250
No, that's not too weird.

1047
01:36:30,152 --> 01:36:32,354
It's beautiful.

1048
01:36:32,387 --> 01:36:36,058
And it's unique, which
certainly fits the situation.

1049
01:36:38,861 --> 01:36:40,062
I like Renesmee.

1050
01:36:45,267 --> 01:36:46,201
He likes it.

1051
01:36:51,874 --> 01:36:53,008
(GASPS)

1052
01:37:08,356 --> 01:37:10,926
EDWARD: Rosalie,
pass the morphine.

1053
01:37:11,526 --> 01:37:12,928
(GASPS)

1054
01:37:12,961 --> 01:37:15,163
Carlisle said the placenta
must have detached.

1055
01:37:15,197 --> 01:37:17,565
(GRUNTS)

1056
01:37:17,599 --> 01:37:19,935
He's coming as fast as he
can, but... We'll have to do it.

1057
01:37:23,138 --> 01:37:26,008
Rose! Let the morphine spread.

1058
01:37:26,041 --> 01:37:27,275
There's no time. He's dying.

1059
01:37:28,210 --> 01:37:29,344
Get him out now!

1060
01:37:31,146 --> 01:37:32,180
Look at me, Bella.

1061
01:37:33,148 --> 01:37:34,282
(BELLA SCREAMING)

1062
01:37:41,223 --> 01:37:42,357
JACOB: Rosalie, don't!

1063
01:37:42,390 --> 01:37:43,591
(SCALPEL CLATTERS)

1064
01:37:43,625 --> 01:37:45,027
Alice, get her out of here!

1065
01:37:45,060 --> 01:37:46,895
(EXCLAIMS) Rosalie!

1066
01:37:48,663 --> 01:37:50,432
Ow! (SCREAMS)

1067
01:37:50,465 --> 01:37:52,067
Save her!
You've got to change her!

1068
01:37:52,100 --> 01:37:53,235
I can't, not whilst
he's still in there.

1069
01:37:53,268 --> 01:37:55,938
I got to get him out first.

1070
01:37:55,971 --> 01:37:58,540
Stay, Bella. Stay focused.
Keep your heart beating.

1071
01:37:58,573 --> 01:38:00,408
No! He's suffocating!

1072
01:38:01,509 --> 01:38:02,544
(SCREAMING)

1073
01:38:14,990 --> 01:38:15,924
EDWARD: Okay.

1074
01:38:27,302 --> 01:38:28,503
(LAUGHS)

1075
01:38:33,541 --> 01:38:34,977
(BABY CRYING)

1076
01:38:36,644 --> 01:38:38,280
EDWARD: Hey.

1077
01:38:38,313 --> 01:38:39,514
Hey, hey.

1078
01:38:41,316 --> 01:38:42,384
It's Renesmee.

1079
01:38:49,024 --> 01:38:50,058
(SIGHING)

1080
01:38:52,327 --> 01:38:54,162
You're beautiful.

1081
01:39:07,075 --> 01:39:08,076
(GROANS)

1082
01:39:09,144 --> 01:39:10,212
(BABY CRIES)

1083
01:39:17,385 --> 01:39:18,453
Hey.

1084
01:39:32,367 --> 01:39:34,369
JACOB: Bella?

1085
01:39:34,402 --> 01:39:35,437
Bella?

1086
01:39:37,139 --> 01:39:38,673
Bella!

1087
01:39:45,380 --> 01:39:47,215
Jacob, take the baby.

1088
01:39:47,249 --> 01:39:48,783
Keep that away from me!

1089
01:39:48,816 --> 01:39:50,785
Edward.

1090
01:39:50,818 --> 01:39:53,221
I'll take her.

1091
01:39:53,255 --> 01:39:55,357
I promise I'm okay. Let me.

1092
01:40:03,498 --> 01:40:04,499
What is that?

1093
01:40:09,237 --> 01:40:10,105
It's my venom.

1094
01:40:23,351 --> 01:40:25,520
(WHISPERING) You're okay.

1095
01:40:28,256 --> 01:40:29,491
Come on.

1096
01:40:37,432 --> 01:40:39,101
It's supposed to be working.

1097
01:40:41,269 --> 01:40:42,604
JACOB: Oh, my God.

1098
01:40:42,637 --> 01:40:43,671
Come on.

1099
01:40:45,407 --> 01:40:47,442
Bella, come on.

1100
01:40:52,880 --> 01:40:55,083
I won't kill you.

1101
01:40:55,117 --> 01:40:57,352
That'd be too easy.

1102
01:40:57,385 --> 01:40:59,721
You deserve to live with this.

1103
01:41:30,318 --> 01:41:31,586
(SOBBING)

1104
01:41:35,390 --> 01:41:36,424
She didn't make it.

1105
01:41:51,273 --> 01:41:53,375
EDWARD: You're not dead.
You're not dead.

1106
01:41:55,177 --> 01:41:55,843
Come on!

1107
01:41:58,213 --> 01:41:59,247
Come on!

1108
01:42:06,788 --> 01:42:10,392
No, it will work.
It will work.

1109
01:42:10,425 --> 01:42:12,460
Please, please, please, please.

1110
01:42:46,928 --> 01:42:47,929
(SCREAMING)

1111
01:42:57,672 --> 01:43:00,475
Come back to me, please, baby.

1112
01:43:00,508 --> 01:43:02,677
Bella, Bella, please, please.

1113
01:43:10,452 --> 01:43:11,486
(BABY COOING)

1114
01:43:11,519 --> 01:43:13,621
Hi, hi.

1115
01:43:33,741 --> 01:43:35,643
I don't care what he's done.

1116
01:43:36,478 --> 01:43:37,912
He's still my son.

1117
01:43:37,945 --> 01:43:40,282
I'm sorry, Billy.

1118
01:43:40,315 --> 01:43:41,349
I just thought you should know.

1119
01:43:47,555 --> 01:43:48,690
Bella's dead.

1120
01:43:50,292 --> 01:43:51,626
It killed her.

1121
01:43:54,729 --> 01:43:56,764
Let's go!

1122
01:44:21,456 --> 01:44:22,657
(SHUSHING)

1123
01:44:44,946 --> 01:44:48,983
JACOB: It's like gravity.

1124
01:44:49,016 --> 01:44:51,419
Your whole center shifts.

1125
01:44:54,389 --> 01:44:58,059
Suddenly, it's not the Earth
holding you here.

1126
01:44:58,092 --> 01:45:02,564
You would do anything,
be anything she needs.

1127
01:45:04,766 --> 01:45:07,969
A friend, a brother.

1128
01:45:09,637 --> 01:45:10,772
A protector.

1129
01:45:23,117 --> 01:45:24,619
(WOLVES GROWLING)

1130
01:45:32,093 --> 01:45:34,729
Alice! Jasper!

1131
01:45:40,602 --> 01:45:42,537
You're gonna be all right.

1132
01:45:51,112 --> 01:45:52,447
Stay with Bella.

1133
01:46:08,496 --> 01:46:09,731
Do it for him.

1134
01:46:10,432 --> 01:46:11,533
Protect him.

1135
01:46:20,975 --> 01:46:22,710
We're outnumbered.
By a lot.

1136
01:46:22,744 --> 01:46:24,145
I won't let them hurt my family.

1137
01:46:32,086 --> 01:46:34,021
(GROWLING)

1138
01:46:41,796 --> 01:46:42,864
(ALICE SCREAMS)

1139
01:46:44,231 --> 01:46:46,934
(EDWARD GRUNTING)

1140
01:46:59,781 --> 01:47:00,815
(JASPER GRUNTS)

1141
01:47:10,224 --> 01:47:12,927
(ALICE SCREAMING)

1142
01:47:37,218 --> 01:47:38,620
(JASPER GRUNTING)

1143
01:47:45,527 --> 01:47:47,028
Stop! It's over!

1144
01:47:48,930 --> 01:47:50,464
If you kill her, you kill me.

1145
01:48:05,647 --> 01:48:06,648
Jacob imprinted.

1146
01:48:12,086 --> 01:48:14,656
They can't hurt her.

1147
01:48:14,689 --> 01:48:17,859
Whoever a wolf imprints
on can't be harmed.

1148
01:48:22,163 --> 01:48:24,932
It's their most absolute law.

1149
01:49:00,902 --> 01:49:04,005
EDWARD:
She shouldn't be this still.

1150
01:49:04,038 --> 01:49:05,072
CARLISLE: It's the morphine.

1151
01:49:07,074 --> 01:49:08,175
EDWARD: Maybe I was too late.

1152
01:49:08,209 --> 01:49:09,210
CARLISLE: No, Edward.

1153
01:49:10,277 --> 01:49:12,079
Listen to her heart.

1154
01:49:40,875 --> 01:49:42,576
(HEART BEATING SLOWLY)

1155
01:50:03,064 --> 01:50:04,231
(HEART BEATING FRANTICALLY)

1156
01:50:19,080 --> 01:50:20,815
(HEART BEATING STEADILY)

1157
01:50:35,997 --> 01:50:37,865
(HEARTBEAT QUICKENS)

1158
01:51:23,110 --> 01:51:24,912
(HEART BEATING STEADILY)

1159
01:51:41,295 --> 01:51:43,030
(HEART STOPS BEATING)

1160
01:52:14,796 --> 01:52:15,396
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

1161
01:53:57,564 --> 01:53:59,300
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

1162
01:54:34,001 --> 01:54:35,269
Ah. It's from Carlisle.

1163
01:54:37,004 --> 01:54:42,276
Which is spelt with an "S,"
Sweet Bianca.

1164
01:54:47,949 --> 01:54:51,118
He's added a new
member to his coven.

1165
01:54:51,152 --> 01:54:52,286
Ah.

1166
01:54:52,319 --> 01:54:54,555
Increasing his power.

1167
01:54:57,959 --> 01:55:00,962
(BIANCA SCREAMING)

1168
01:55:03,697 --> 01:55:05,499
First it's the spelling,

1169
01:55:06,433 --> 01:55:08,069
then the grammar.

1170
01:55:10,671 --> 01:55:15,442
At least our dispute
with the Cullens is over.

1171
01:55:16,477 --> 01:55:18,379
Over?
Mmm.

1172
01:55:18,412 --> 01:55:21,382
Goodness, no.

1173
01:55:21,415 --> 01:55:25,987
Our dispute goes far beyond
the fate of a mere human.

1174
01:55:27,321 --> 01:55:29,356
And what might it be?

1175
01:55:29,390 --> 01:55:31,993
Why, brother,
I thought you understood.

1176
01:55:34,061 --> 01:55:36,130
They have something I want.

1177
01:55:40,034 --> 01:55:42,003
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1178
01:59:49,316 --> 01:59:51,952
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

